    public class MainActivity
extends android.support.v7.app.AppCompatActivity
    MainActivity is the main screen we can see when launching app for the first time. It creates periodical job and allows user to read information from app. MainActivity also allows user to change wifi SSID regex and to view and edit entries from last 3 months

      • onCreate

        protected void onCreate(android.os.Bundle savedInstanceState)
        Invoked when MainActivity is created when opening the app. We also start services here. (Broadcast Receiver, to detect wifi state change and FileManipulator to fetch data from our application proto files) BroadcastReceiver Service is never closed, and FileManipulator Service is closed with MainActivity
        Overrides:
        onCreate in class android.support.v7.app.AppCompatActivity
        Parameters:
        savedInstanceState - used by super.

      • onStart

        protected void onStart()
        Invoked right before actually displaying out application to user. We make sure that when onStart finishes, we are already in process of binding to 2 services we are using, and that we actually scheduled a job
        Overrides:
        onStart in class android.support.v7.app.AppCompatActivity

      • onStop

      • refresh

        public void refresh(android.view.View view)
        Function run when user clicks "refresh" button. It forces BroadcastReceiver Server to save its data and then forces FileManipulator Service to invalidate last calculated values, after which it refreshes the screen so user can see current, correct values
        Parameters:
        view - - it's the clicked button

      • refreshValues

        private void refreshValues()
        Used to refresh all fields in activity_main with currently calculated values. The fields we are updating are: todayTicker - how long have we been connected to wifi for today average7Data - average connection time for last 7 (not zero) days average30Data - average connection time for last 30 (not zero) days average90Data - average connection time for last 90 (not zero) days

      • requestLocationPermission

        private void requestLocationPermission()
        Asks user for permission to access coarse location. If user previously disallowed, we show an explanation and ask again Access to coarse location is needed to read SSID of connected network. This is true as of android 8.1.0 (API 27) and later

      • scheduleJob

        private void scheduleJob()
        Scheduler a job that is executed approx. every 15 minutes with 1m flex time. Also this job is set to be Persisted, that means it stays between reboots.
